1. If your header files should be shared between MTEE and Linux Kernel, 
   those header files should be put in the folders both below.
   1-1. alps/mediatek/kernel/include/trustzone/tz_cross
   1-2. alps/mediatek/trustzone/mtk/include/tz_cross

2. If your header files should be shared between MTEE, Linux Kernel and Linux User Space
   those header files should be put in the folders both below.
   2-1. alps/mediatek/kernel/include/trustzone/tz_cross
   2-2. alps/mediatek/trustzone/mtk/include/tz_cross

3. If your header files should be shared between MTEE and Linux User Space
   those header files should be put in the folders both below.
   3-1. alps/mediatek/trustzone/mtk/include/tz_cross

4. It is noted that head files in Linux Kernel should not include MTK License Disclaimer
